WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:05.400


00:00:07.721 --> 00:00:09.481
[If you don't turn yourself in,
your limbs will rot and you'll die]

00:00:37.938 --> 00:00:41.298
[All characters and events are fictional,
and any resemblance is coincidental]

00:00:41.298 --> 00:00:43.905
[Scenes with children and animals were filmed
safely under professional supervision]

00:00:43.905 --> 00:00:48.338
But please tell me your story too.

00:00:48.338 --> 00:00:51.038
It's no fun if I'm the only one talking.

00:00:51.038 --> 00:00:53.105
You tell yours,

00:00:53.105 --> 00:00:54.805
and I'll tell mine.

00:00:54.805 --> 00:00:59.738
That way, we can complete our story.

00:00:59.738 --> 00:01:01.038
"Our story"?

00:01:01.038 --> 00:01:04.038
Yes, ours.

00:01:13.838 --> 00:01:18.172
First, tell me about the person
you said you hated the most.

00:01:18.172 --> 00:01:22.072
When you first met them,
and why you came to hate them.

00:01:25.505 --> 00:01:28.138
Come on.

00:01:28.138 --> 00:01:30.505
You didn't hate them
from the beginning, did you?

00:01:32.772 --> 00:01:34.572
From what I've seen in life,

00:01:34.572 --> 00:01:37.705
hatred doesn't just appear out of nowhere.

00:01:37.705 --> 00:01:40.805
To build up like that, there has
to be something underneath first.

00:01:40.805 --> 00:01:43.638
Friendship, affection, something like that.

00:01:43.638 --> 00:01:48.738
And it's only when something like that
gets crushed that hatred arises.

00:02:14.672 --> 00:02:17.672
[Episode 4]

00:02:52.838 --> 00:02:55.238
[Examination Room]
It's still a case of strangulation.

00:02:56.338 --> 00:02:59.938
But something feels off.

00:02:59.938 --> 00:03:01.772
What is it?

00:03:02.438 --> 00:03:04.672
What's different about this case is that...

00:03:12.972 --> 00:03:16.738
The chest was slashed with a razor blade.

00:03:19.938 --> 00:03:21.705
It's the first time
the perpetrator has done this.

00:03:27.005 --> 00:03:29.572
Was that done
while the victim was still alive?

00:03:32.451 --> 00:03:34.921
Oh, well...

00:03:34.921 --> 00:03:36.972
And this was found inside the body.

00:03:38.638 --> 00:03:41.038
He stuffed the genitals with it.

00:03:45.538 --> 00:03:47.205
What's that?

00:03:55.938 --> 00:03:57.405
What's this?

00:03:57.405 --> 00:03:59.238
It's a bribe.

00:04:16.745 --> 00:04:23.332
[Restricted Area, Authorized Personnel Only]

00:04:26.205 --> 00:04:28.505
Don't dwell on it. Just go.

00:04:28.505 --> 00:04:30.472
It's not your case anymore.

00:04:31.772 --> 00:04:33.372
Cha Si Young!

00:04:34.772 --> 00:04:36.372
Si Young.

00:04:39.638 --> 00:04:42.038
I've got to catch that punk.

00:04:46.972 --> 00:04:48.805
Let's catch him together.

00:04:51.805 --> 00:04:53.438
Together?

00:04:54.872 --> 00:04:56.938
Yeah.

00:04:56.938 --> 00:04:58.572
Together.

00:05:01.272 --> 00:05:03.138
Shall we be friends?

00:05:04.838 --> 00:05:06.238
I heard you're smart.

00:05:06.238 --> 00:05:08.072
I am too.

00:05:08.072 --> 00:05:10.105
Wouldn't it be nice if we could be friends?

00:05:11.438 --> 00:05:13.272
I don't need friends.

00:05:14.572 --> 00:05:16.172
Then what about money?

00:05:20.738 --> 00:05:22.438
Want to tutor me?

00:05:23.205 --> 00:05:24.805
I'll pay you.

00:05:27.497 --> 00:05:30.137
Give it here.

00:05:31.017 --> 00:05:33.338
Try solving this.

00:05:33.338 --> 00:05:34.338
Here.

00:05:34.338 --> 00:05:37.005
Oh, right. This is it.

00:05:42.038 --> 00:05:44.005
What?

00:05:44.005 --> 00:05:45.638
You got it right!

00:05:48.238 --> 00:05:49.805
You explain things really well.

00:05:49.805 --> 00:05:50.938
Maybe even better than my math teacher.

00:05:50.938 --> 00:05:53.072
It's just that he's bad at it.

00:05:54.205 --> 00:05:55.305
I need the bathroom.

00:05:55.305 --> 00:05:56.905
Bathroom?

00:05:57.972 --> 00:05:59.205
Solve this for me.

00:05:59.205 --> 00:06:00.838
Okay.

00:06:25.705 --> 00:06:27.372
Try this.

00:06:34.238 --> 00:06:35.872
It's delicious.

00:06:35.872 --> 00:06:38.205
Tae Joo, where did you get this?

00:06:38.205 --> 00:06:40.138
My friend gave me this.

00:06:40.138 --> 00:06:43.605
That's a good friend. Ask for more, okay?

00:06:43.605 --> 00:06:45.438
Okay.

00:06:45.438 --> 00:06:47.038
Eat up.

00:07:13.972 --> 00:07:15.705
- You're leaving?
- Yeah.

00:07:15.705 --> 00:07:17.338
Tae Joo.

00:07:18.172 --> 00:07:19.805
Huh?

00:07:21.172 --> 00:07:23.465
Let's go

00:07:23.465 --> 00:07:25.539
to the same college.

00:07:27.272 --> 00:07:28.905
Okay.

00:07:32.038 --> 00:07:33.638
Get home safely.

00:07:35.472 --> 00:07:37.105
Oh, right.

00:07:37.929 --> 00:07:41.027
[Middle School Mathematics]

00:07:41.027 --> 00:07:42.505
Jeez.

00:07:42.505 --> 00:07:44.305
I forgot.

00:07:46.238 --> 00:07:48.005
Well, I'll give it to him next time.

00:07:50.538 --> 00:07:52.738
Why are you so late?

00:07:52.738 --> 00:07:55.138
Get Sun Young something to eat.
She's been whining since earlier.

00:07:55.138 --> 00:07:56.738
Mom!

00:07:59.438 --> 00:08:01.905
Can I go to college?

00:08:01.905 --> 00:08:05.172
Go, earn the money and go.

00:08:14.538 --> 00:08:16.138
Si Young!

00:08:20.138 --> 00:08:22.005
You've got something there.

00:08:22.005 --> 00:08:23.938
Keep your hands off me.

00:08:24.772 --> 00:08:26.405
So filthy.

00:08:26.405 --> 00:08:28.805
- What's wrong?
- Stop it!

00:08:31.772 --> 00:08:34.238
Why didn't you tell me?

00:08:34.238 --> 00:08:36.405
That your mom works as a hostess?

00:08:41.172 --> 00:08:43.638
Do you want me to spill

00:08:43.638 --> 00:08:45.405
who you really are?

00:08:46.472 --> 00:08:48.672
Everyone should know what they need to know.

00:08:51.672 --> 00:08:53.905
Please don't say anything.

00:08:53.905 --> 00:08:55.572
I'm begging you.

00:09:05.272 --> 00:09:07.405
Then will you do whatever I say?

00:09:08.705 --> 00:09:10.338
Yeah.

00:09:14.472 --> 00:09:16.138
Anything?

00:09:16.938 --> 00:09:18.572
Anything.

00:09:27.738 --> 00:09:31.638
[Bang Kyung Moon Clinic]

00:09:32.805 --> 00:09:34.872
Si Young.

00:09:34.872 --> 00:09:36.638
Let's catch him together.

00:09:37.472 --> 00:09:39.072
Together?

00:09:43.072 --> 00:09:44.705
Together.

00:09:46.905 --> 00:09:48.505
That sounds nice.

00:09:50.472 --> 00:09:52.072
Let's give it a shot.

00:09:52.738 --> 00:09:54.105
[The police let the suspect slip
right past them]

00:09:54.105 --> 00:09:55.372
Take a look.

00:09:55.372 --> 00:09:58.105
They say this is
what the serial killer looks like.

00:09:59.372 --> 00:10:03.105
We didn't even see a strand of his hair.
Does that make any sense?

00:10:03.105 --> 00:10:05.372
We did see his hair.

00:10:05.372 --> 00:10:07.272
We also got his blood type from there.

00:10:07.272 --> 00:10:10.705
So you're proud of
just getting his blood type?

00:10:10.705 --> 00:10:14.172
We're already checking people
with similar priors.

00:10:14.172 --> 00:10:17.545
- We'll catch him soon enough.
- Darn it.

00:10:19.138 --> 00:10:21.372
So, what evidence did you find in this case?

00:10:22.938 --> 00:10:24.338
I said, what did you get?

00:10:24.338 --> 00:10:25.738
Not much, sir.

00:10:25.738 --> 00:10:30.705
Hair, body hair, bloodstains
from the clothes, all type B.

00:10:30.705 --> 00:10:34.105
Mr. Kim, you got a problem with me?

00:10:37.472 --> 00:10:38.838
I said, any problem with that?

00:10:38.838 --> 00:10:40.938
- No, sir.
- It sounds like you do.

00:10:40.938 --> 00:10:42.605
What is it?

00:10:44.572 --> 00:10:46.185
Chief,

00:10:46.185 --> 00:10:49.838
could you hold off
on processing Kang Tae Joo's resignation?

00:10:49.838 --> 00:10:52.238
Jeon Kyeong Ho's medical report was forged,

00:10:52.238 --> 00:10:55.005
- and...
- Did you even read this article?

00:10:55.005 --> 00:10:57.172
Who's the one that let the killer slip?

00:10:57.172 --> 00:10:59.705
It's Kang Tae Joo! Kang Tae Joo!

00:11:01.505 --> 00:11:04.272
Hello, Detective Chief Heo
of Kangseng Police.

00:11:04.272 --> 00:11:06.372
Yes.

00:11:06.372 --> 00:11:07.372
Just a moment, please.

00:11:07.372 --> 00:11:08.972
Chief.

00:11:09.738 --> 00:11:11.433
Hello?

00:11:11.433 --> 00:11:13.105
Who is this?

00:11:14.972 --> 00:11:18.505
Yes, this is Park Eun Kyu,
Chief of Kangseng Police.

00:11:18.505 --> 00:11:20.905
Yes, go ahead, Superintendent.

00:11:21.972 --> 00:11:23.338
- Superintendent?
- What?

00:11:23.338 --> 00:11:25.472
You mean Kang Tae Joo?

00:11:29.305 --> 00:11:30.953
That can't be.

00:11:30.953 --> 00:11:33.538
His resignation hasn't
even been accepted yet.

00:11:36.803 --> 00:11:38.011
[Gyeongbuk apples]

00:11:42.572 --> 00:11:45.172
You're back? How?

00:11:46.638 --> 00:11:49.572
Maybe the Chief's been too busy.

00:11:49.572 --> 00:11:52.105
It seems
my resignation hasn't been processed yet.

00:11:52.105 --> 00:11:53.838
That's even possible?

00:11:55.011 --> 00:11:57.205
Hey!

00:11:57.205 --> 00:11:59.338
That hurt? Come with me.

00:12:08.405 --> 00:12:10.705
Hey, what's going on?

00:12:10.705 --> 00:12:13.205
Tell me everything in detail.

00:12:13.205 --> 00:12:16.772
We're short-staffed anyway,
so just take it as a stroke of luck.

00:12:16.772 --> 00:12:18.638
That's not the point.

00:12:18.638 --> 00:12:22.772
Why would a superintendent step in
over a sergeant's resignation?

00:12:22.772 --> 00:12:24.205
A superintendent?

00:12:24.205 --> 00:12:27.105
What, you didn't know, either? Seriously?

00:12:27.105 --> 00:12:29.238
Well...

00:12:29.238 --> 00:12:30.338
Who's this senior superintendent?

00:12:30.338 --> 00:12:31.338
Cha Jun Young.

00:12:31.338 --> 00:12:33.138
You don't know Superintendent Cha Jun Young?

00:12:33.138 --> 00:12:35.272
The youngest ever
to become a superintendent in Korea.

00:12:35.272 --> 00:12:39.715
He's currently on assignment
at the Blue House, and he's a big shot.

00:12:39.715 --> 00:12:43.049
Well, a superintendent?

00:12:43.049 --> 00:12:44.905
That's huge.

00:12:46.838 --> 00:12:50.205
Seriously, is he backing you?

00:12:52.372 --> 00:12:53.705
Let's just say he is.

00:12:53.705 --> 00:12:55.872
It's not entirely wrong.

00:13:00.305 --> 00:13:02.217
What is he talking about?

00:13:02.217 --> 00:13:03.433
Wow.

00:13:03.433 --> 00:13:06.972
A superintendent stepping in
over a low-ranking cop.

00:13:07.605 --> 00:13:09.238
I'm sorry.

00:13:10.905 --> 00:13:15.738
This Kang Tae Joo or whatever his name is,
he'd better be worth it.

00:13:15.738 --> 00:13:17.772
He will be.

00:13:18.972 --> 00:13:21.005
And the Kangseng Serial Murder Case.

00:13:21.005 --> 00:13:24.405
Don't let anyone else steal it.
Finish it with your own hands.

00:13:24.405 --> 00:13:27.038
Father is preparing for the election,
so if you can't help,

00:13:27.038 --> 00:13:29.638
at least don't be a liability, got it?

00:13:30.405 --> 00:13:32.338
I'll keep that in mind.

00:13:32.338 --> 00:13:33.609
Good,

00:13:33.609 --> 00:13:35.305
make sure you do that.

00:13:38.538 --> 00:13:41.938
I heard you're seeing
Chairman Kim Tae Seop's daughter lately?

00:13:44.272 --> 00:13:46.972
She seems like a fine woman.

00:13:47.619 --> 00:13:49.241
Jeez.

00:13:50.305 --> 00:13:51.738
What,

00:13:51.738 --> 00:13:55.038
you're trying to go into politics too?

00:14:01.105 --> 00:14:03.238
Well, Cha Si Young.

00:14:05.138 --> 00:14:08.105
You know what happens
when a sparrow chases a stork?

00:14:09.105 --> 00:14:11.805
It gets torn apart.

00:14:12.841 --> 00:14:16.272
You're old enough to know your place.

00:14:16.272 --> 00:14:19.705
Why is that so hard for you?

00:14:19.705 --> 00:14:21.472
I don't get it.

00:14:40.105 --> 00:14:43.672
Hey, you finished the list
of Kim Min Ji's belongings?

00:14:43.672 --> 00:14:45.272
Not yet.

00:14:46.238 --> 00:14:49.438
What about her movements that day?
Did you check?

00:14:49.438 --> 00:14:51.638
Not that, either.

00:14:51.638 --> 00:14:54.272
Then what exactly have you been doing?

00:14:56.905 --> 00:14:59.625
I don't think someone
who quit and then came back

00:14:59.625 --> 00:15:02.438
can say that to me.

00:15:03.772 --> 00:15:05.438
What's wrong with him?

00:15:05.438 --> 00:15:07.138
Heatstroke?

00:15:12.005 --> 00:15:13.605
Park Dae Ho!

00:15:15.305 --> 00:15:16.905
Come out.

00:15:19.872 --> 00:15:21.572
Rookie,

00:15:21.572 --> 00:15:22.872
just apologize.

00:15:22.872 --> 00:15:26.205
Apologize for what? Since you've already
gone this far, just go all in.

00:15:26.205 --> 00:15:27.972
You punk.

00:15:37.172 --> 00:15:40.772
That guy's got guts.

00:15:48.572 --> 00:15:50.172
Eat up.

00:15:55.038 --> 00:15:57.838
Go on. Why are you mad at me?

00:15:59.038 --> 00:16:01.472
- I'm not.
- Seems you are.

00:16:01.472 --> 00:16:03.105
Say it.

00:16:12.572 --> 00:16:14.205
Honestly,

00:16:15.005 --> 00:16:17.038
I was disappointed.

00:16:17.038 --> 00:16:19.472
Because you quit too easily.

00:16:19.472 --> 00:16:21.372
After you came,

00:16:21.372 --> 00:16:24.038
I learned what to focus on in cases,

00:16:24.038 --> 00:16:26.372
and how to approach suspects.

00:16:26.372 --> 00:16:27.905
I learned those things

00:16:27.905 --> 00:16:30.205
and I wanted to learn more and do better.

00:16:30.205 --> 00:16:33.738
I really wanted to catch the killer
together with you.

00:16:33.738 --> 00:16:36.605
I assumed you felt the same. But...

00:16:36.605 --> 00:16:38.472
I just ran off, huh?

00:16:41.472 --> 00:16:43.105
But

00:16:44.172 --> 00:16:46.705
I didn't quit easily.

00:16:48.872 --> 00:16:51.372
It was really hard for me to quit.

00:16:52.172 --> 00:16:53.805
And...

00:16:55.205 --> 00:16:58.038
coming back was even harder than that.

00:16:59.438 --> 00:17:02.409
I had to give up a lot

00:17:02.409 --> 00:17:04.372
to get back in.

00:17:06.638 --> 00:17:07.705
What did you have to give up?

00:17:07.705 --> 00:17:10.038
That's none of your business.

00:17:11.472 --> 00:17:13.432
I met Min Ji

00:17:13.432 --> 00:17:15.538
the other day.

00:17:17.172 --> 00:17:22.272
She told me not to quit.
Otherwise, who would catch the suspect?

00:17:22.272 --> 00:17:24.872
She told me to catch the suspect.

00:17:24.872 --> 00:17:27.838
[Kangseng Bookstore]
Can't you not quit being a cop?

00:17:27.838 --> 00:17:30.972
I want you to catch him yourself, sir.

00:17:30.972 --> 00:17:32.238
It's a bribe.

00:17:32.238 --> 00:17:35.472
When you eat it,
just think it over twice more.

00:17:35.472 --> 00:17:38.105
Okay? Bye!

00:17:41.738 --> 00:17:44.505
So that's why you came back?

00:17:44.505 --> 00:17:46.138
No.

00:17:48.105 --> 00:17:50.505
I just can't take it anymore

00:17:52.338 --> 00:17:54.572
unless I catch that guy.

00:17:56.538 --> 00:17:58.405
That's why I came back.

00:18:01.972 --> 00:18:04.105
So cut me some slack.

00:18:04.105 --> 00:18:06.605
Who am I to do that?

00:18:08.872 --> 00:18:11.872
I'm sorry I was sulking, sir.

00:18:11.872 --> 00:18:16.138
And I'm glad you're back.

00:18:20.538 --> 00:18:23.038
This place is really good, eat up.

00:18:27.538 --> 00:18:31.405
[National Saemaeul Leaders Convention]

00:18:31.405 --> 00:18:33.505
Hey, Detective Kang!

00:18:33.505 --> 00:18:35.572
I almost forgot your face.
How many years has it been?

00:18:35.572 --> 00:18:39.472
Wow, you haven't aged a bit. Still the same.

00:18:39.472 --> 00:18:41.038
Has your son been discharged?

00:18:41.038 --> 00:18:43.772
That was ages ago.

00:18:43.772 --> 00:18:46.505
Don't ask when you don't even care.

00:18:46.505 --> 00:18:47.972
By the way, the total is off.

00:18:47.972 --> 00:18:49.372
We had two bowls.

00:18:49.372 --> 00:18:51.238
Why are you paying for my son's jjajangmyeon?

00:18:51.238 --> 00:18:52.572
Who's your son?

00:18:52.572 --> 00:18:53.672
Huh?

00:18:53.672 --> 00:18:55.272
Him!

00:18:55.272 --> 00:18:56.672
This is my family's place.

00:18:56.672 --> 00:18:59.638
It's Dae Ho Chinese Restaurant.
Didn't you know?

00:19:01.638 --> 00:19:04.072
He's my junior.

00:19:04.072 --> 00:19:05.138
I'll pay for him, ma'am.

00:19:05.138 --> 00:19:08.672
Alright, thanks for the meal.
We're heading out.

00:19:08.672 --> 00:19:10.905
Mom, I'm off!

00:19:10.905 --> 00:19:12.772
Sir, let's go together!

00:19:12.772 --> 00:19:14.905
Look how happy he is.

00:19:16.272 --> 00:19:18.272
Sir, wait for me!

00:19:25.672 --> 00:19:29.438
[Exclusive: Face of Kangseng
Serial Murder Suspect Obtained]

00:19:31.938 --> 00:19:33.838
There might still be a way.

00:19:33.838 --> 00:19:34.905
What way?

00:19:34.905 --> 00:19:36.713
Well,

00:19:36.713 --> 00:19:38.905
I'll let you know when I'm certain.

00:19:38.905 --> 00:19:43.805
I'm going to help you catch the suspect,
so just wait.

00:19:45.372 --> 00:19:47.772
Unbelievable, Seo Ji Won.

00:20:07.705 --> 00:20:11.605
[The police let the suspect slip
right past them]

00:20:24.538 --> 00:20:27.472
[Kangseng Daily]
Hey, don't get it wrong.

00:20:27.472 --> 00:20:29.505
I didn't write that article, okay?

00:20:29.505 --> 00:20:31.405
I know perfectly well
you lost him because of me that day.

00:20:31.405 --> 00:20:34.305
So how could I write an article like that?
Right?

00:20:34.305 --> 00:20:35.338
But it was your byline.

00:20:35.338 --> 00:20:38.838
The editor changed it
without even telling me.

00:20:38.838 --> 00:20:41.321
I didn't come here to argue about that.

00:20:41.321 --> 00:20:43.805
Just give me the photo.

00:20:43.805 --> 00:20:45.481
Yeah, this is it.

00:20:53.738 --> 00:20:57.838
By the way, why didn't you tell me
you went to school with Mr. Cha?

00:20:57.838 --> 00:20:58.872
What's the big deal?

00:20:58.872 --> 00:21:01.338
He said he wanted to get close to you.

00:21:01.338 --> 00:21:05.105
Didn't he send me that recording to help you?

00:21:05.105 --> 00:21:07.105
There was no camera at the scene.

00:21:07.105 --> 00:21:08.705
Oh.

00:21:09.772 --> 00:21:12.872
I hid it midway,
so the suspect wouldn't notice.

00:21:12.872 --> 00:21:14.272
Why are you only telling me this now?

00:21:14.272 --> 00:21:15.805
What else could I do?

00:21:15.805 --> 00:21:18.472
The police found nothing that day,
and you were cornered.

00:21:18.472 --> 00:21:22.705
Was I supposed to ask you
to find a camera the killer might have taken too?

00:21:25.505 --> 00:21:27.705
Is this that punk?

00:21:27.705 --> 00:21:30.905
Yeah, it's shaky. But see this?

00:21:30.905 --> 00:21:32.672
He covered his face.

00:21:33.805 --> 00:21:35.638
Ms. Kim Mi Yeon didn't mention that.

00:21:35.638 --> 00:21:39.238
So he only covered his face
in front of me? Why?

00:21:45.372 --> 00:21:47.205
This handkerchief looks familiar.

00:21:47.205 --> 00:21:51.705
It is a bit unusual,
but this alone isn't enough to find the suspect.

00:21:51.705 --> 00:21:53.438
True.

00:21:59.505 --> 00:22:04.338
Taking a leave?
The kids must be really disappointed.

00:22:05.105 --> 00:22:06.405
Sorry, I feel bad.

00:22:06.405 --> 00:22:07.705
Don't be.

00:22:07.705 --> 00:22:10.338
Just take a short break and come back.

00:22:10.338 --> 00:22:11.849
Okay,

00:22:11.849 --> 00:22:13.405
I'll come back for my things later.

00:22:13.405 --> 00:22:14.438
Alright.

00:22:14.438 --> 00:22:17.372
- Thank you.
- Yeah, go ahead.

00:22:22.305 --> 00:22:25.572
Are you that busy lately?

00:22:25.572 --> 00:22:27.638
I might forget your face at this rate.

00:22:29.005 --> 00:22:30.305
Oh, sorry.

00:22:30.305 --> 00:22:32.905
I should've been more thoughtful,

00:22:32.905 --> 00:22:34.872
but the cases just keep coming.

00:22:34.872 --> 00:22:37.672
I know it's because of the cases.

00:22:37.672 --> 00:22:41.038
I'm not that inconsiderate.

00:22:41.838 --> 00:22:43.872
But you could've at least called.

00:22:43.872 --> 00:22:47.438
Alright. I'll call you every day from now on.

00:22:47.438 --> 00:22:50.572
No, not every day.

00:22:50.572 --> 00:22:53.672
Just once in a while when you think of me.

00:22:54.705 --> 00:22:57.225
Then I guess I'll have to call you every day.

00:22:59.672 --> 00:23:03.238
Stop it, you're really embarrassing me.

00:23:03.238 --> 00:23:05.205
Stop teasing me.

00:23:09.705 --> 00:23:11.638
You're heading home, right?

00:23:11.638 --> 00:23:13.605
I'll give you a ride.

00:23:14.572 --> 00:23:16.905
If you're going out of your way,
I'd rather not.

00:23:16.905 --> 00:23:20.838
I'm not. I just want to
spend more time with you.

00:23:23.238 --> 00:23:25.417
Oh my, Hee Jin!

00:23:26.772 --> 00:23:27.805
It's been a while.

00:23:27.805 --> 00:23:29.438
Who is he?

00:23:31.438 --> 00:23:33.805
Prosecutor Cha Si Young.

00:23:33.805 --> 00:23:35.438
Prosecutor...

00:23:36.205 --> 00:23:39.272
Oh my, I didn't know there was
such a handsome prosecutor.

00:23:39.272 --> 00:23:40.972
Hey, you sure picked a good one.

00:23:40.972 --> 00:23:43.338
Thank you for the compliment.

00:23:43.338 --> 00:23:48.572
Since you're a prosecutor,
you must have single colleagues, huh?

00:23:48.572 --> 00:23:51.705
- I do.
- Then please introduce me to some.

00:23:51.705 --> 00:23:52.705
Sure.

00:23:52.705 --> 00:23:57.272
But Si Young's been swamped lately.
Not sure he has time for that.

00:23:57.272 --> 00:24:00.272
You know, the serial murders?

00:24:00.272 --> 00:24:02.205
That's his case.

00:24:03.205 --> 00:24:04.905
Well, if he ever has time...

00:24:04.905 --> 00:24:06.672
Si Young, you said you are busy, right?

00:24:06.672 --> 00:24:08.305
We should go.

00:24:08.305 --> 00:24:09.938
See you next time.

00:24:16.738 --> 00:24:19.538
I guess you weren't that close after all.

00:24:20.572 --> 00:24:22.505
Was it that obvious?

00:24:22.505 --> 00:24:23.772
It was really obvious.

00:24:23.772 --> 00:24:25.838
Oh no.

00:24:26.672 --> 00:24:31.405
We were close in middle school,
but we just drifted apart somehow.

00:24:31.405 --> 00:24:33.538
"Somehow"?

00:24:33.538 --> 00:24:36.038
Turns out

00:24:36.038 --> 00:24:39.038
her mom was a mistress.

00:24:39.938 --> 00:24:41.805
How vulgar.

00:24:43.105 --> 00:24:46.605
If I'd known earlier,
I wouldn't have been close to her.

00:24:51.038 --> 00:24:53.038
Where did you park?

00:24:56.205 --> 00:24:58.238
Sorry,

00:24:58.238 --> 00:25:02.172
I forgot I have a meeting this afternoon.

00:25:02.172 --> 00:25:05.138
I'm sorry, but I think I need to go now.

00:25:05.138 --> 00:25:07.205
You can get home by yourself, right?

00:25:07.205 --> 00:25:09.038
My apologies.

00:25:09.038 --> 00:25:10.638
Si Young!

00:25:14.405 --> 00:25:16.205
What's going on?

00:25:24.905 --> 00:25:29.705
[Certificate: Cha Jun Young]

00:25:31.905 --> 00:25:34.305
From now on, you'll live in this house.

00:25:34.305 --> 00:25:36.338
With your father and your brother.

00:25:36.338 --> 00:25:37.605
How does that sound?

00:25:37.605 --> 00:25:39.305
My brother?

00:25:39.305 --> 00:25:43.238
Si Young, you should
study hard like your brother.

00:25:43.238 --> 00:25:44.838
Okay?

00:25:49.738 --> 00:25:53.672
Mom, who is that?

00:25:56.867 --> 00:25:57.938
Jeez.

00:25:57.938 --> 00:25:59.705
- Hey, sir.
- Yes?

00:25:59.705 --> 00:26:02.238
Take that off, quickly!

00:26:02.238 --> 00:26:04.338
No, not that! The photo!

00:26:04.338 --> 00:26:05.972
Okay.

00:26:20.072 --> 00:26:22.172
Miss, are you okay?

00:26:22.172 --> 00:26:24.838
- Yes. Thank you.
- Oh my.

00:26:24.838 --> 00:26:26.538
Are you alright?

00:26:26.538 --> 00:26:27.638
Oh, yes.

00:26:27.638 --> 00:26:28.772
Not hurt?

00:26:28.772 --> 00:26:30.438
No.

00:26:30.438 --> 00:26:31.538
- Thank you.
- Sure you're okay?

00:26:31.538 --> 00:26:33.838
Yes, I'm fine.

00:26:33.838 --> 00:26:37.897
Oh? You're my brother's friend, right?

00:26:39.538 --> 00:26:41.505
But are you really okay?

00:26:41.505 --> 00:26:43.105
Let's go to the hospital just in case.

00:26:43.105 --> 00:26:45.353
No, I'm really fine.

00:26:45.353 --> 00:26:46.910
Huh?

00:26:49.513 --> 00:26:52.372
- Huh?
- I said I'm fine...

00:26:54.838 --> 00:26:57.205
Where did that pretty sound come from?

00:26:58.305 --> 00:27:01.027
You don't seem fine at all.

00:27:03.972 --> 00:27:06.738
[Italian Bakery]

00:27:06.738 --> 00:27:08.738
Here, have some.

00:27:08.738 --> 00:27:11.705
Oh, this is a lot.

00:27:12.905 --> 00:27:16.372
From what I heard, it sounded pretty urgent,

00:27:16.372 --> 00:27:18.238
so maybe you should grab a bite.

00:27:20.738 --> 00:27:23.472
Oh, how embarrassing.

00:27:26.505 --> 00:27:29.775
It's kind of sad that I'm feeling hungry

00:27:29.775 --> 00:27:32.172
even in a situation like this.

00:27:32.172 --> 00:27:34.505
What situation?

00:27:34.505 --> 00:27:36.738
I've taken a leave from school.

00:27:36.738 --> 00:27:38.249
Why?

00:27:38.857 --> 00:27:41.872
Is it because of Jeon Kyeong Ho?

00:27:41.872 --> 00:27:44.072
Didn't he already quit the school?

00:27:45.438 --> 00:27:47.572
That has nothing to do with it.

00:27:47.572 --> 00:27:50.305
I just wanted to take a break.

00:27:53.172 --> 00:27:55.938
I don't have any specific plans yet.

00:27:55.938 --> 00:27:58.338
Please don't tell my brother.

00:28:02.403 --> 00:28:04.105
[Italian Bakery]

00:28:04.105 --> 00:28:06.072
Sun Young!

00:28:06.072 --> 00:28:07.938
I packed it since you barely ate.

00:28:07.938 --> 00:28:09.472
Plenty of castella.

00:28:09.472 --> 00:28:11.017
You like it, right?

00:28:11.017 --> 00:28:13.205
[Italian Bakery]

00:28:13.205 --> 00:28:14.238
How did you know?

00:28:14.238 --> 00:28:18.772
Back then, Tae Joo used
to take snacks for you a lot.

00:28:20.073 --> 00:28:23.538
Oh, so you're the one
who'd pack snacks for me...

00:28:24.305 --> 00:28:26.038
You remember, huh?

00:28:27.238 --> 00:28:29.572
You must've meant a lot to him.

00:28:29.572 --> 00:28:31.205
Me?

00:28:31.205 --> 00:28:34.472
It's not easy to care
for a friend's sibling, you know.

00:28:35.405 --> 00:28:37.005
Is that so?

00:28:37.938 --> 00:28:40.338
Let's go. I'll take you home.

00:28:40.338 --> 00:28:41.938
No, it's okay.

00:28:41.938 --> 00:28:45.105
I just feel bad.

00:28:45.105 --> 00:28:46.572
I'm not very comfortable

00:28:46.572 --> 00:28:48.713
getting in a car alone with a man.

00:28:52.105 --> 00:28:54.872
I'll enjoy this, thank you.

00:28:57.605 --> 00:28:59.972
- Then...
- You go ahead.

00:28:59.972 --> 00:29:01.605
Take care.

00:29:37.091 --> 00:29:38.665
- Darn you.
- Oh, wait...

00:29:39.491 --> 00:29:41.005
Please wait!

00:29:41.005 --> 00:29:43.405
What's your problem? Why are you doing this?

00:29:43.405 --> 00:29:45.505
It was you, right? You hit Sun Young?

00:29:45.505 --> 00:29:49.938
Do you even know
what kind of humiliation she went through?

00:29:49.938 --> 00:29:51.405
I'm a victim too.

00:29:51.405 --> 00:29:53.105
And I didn't mean for it to happen like that.

00:29:53.105 --> 00:29:54.205
You punk!

00:29:54.205 --> 00:29:56.638
I... I was wrong.

00:29:56.638 --> 00:29:58.772
Please forgive me, I'm begging you.

00:29:58.772 --> 00:30:00.772
You should be asking Sun Young
for forgiveness.

00:30:00.772 --> 00:30:03.238
You don't even know
what kind of woman she is, do you?

00:30:03.238 --> 00:30:05.038
You're being fooled too.

00:30:05.038 --> 00:30:08.438
I just saw her fooling
around with another guy.

00:30:08.438 --> 00:30:10.538
Shut up!

00:30:10.538 --> 00:30:12.272
She's such a tramp!

00:30:12.272 --> 00:30:14.972
She just goes around
seeing different guys, no matter who it is.

00:30:14.972 --> 00:30:16.705
I said shut up!

00:30:18.851 --> 00:30:20.617
Darn you!

00:30:21.539 --> 00:30:23.177
No, wait...

00:30:25.161 --> 00:30:27.849
Darn you!

00:30:33.772 --> 00:30:34.905
Go to hell!

00:30:34.905 --> 00:30:37.038
Go to hell, you punk!

00:30:37.038 --> 00:30:38.672
Go to hell!

00:30:42.972 --> 00:30:45.238
He covered his face?

00:30:46.205 --> 00:30:47.872
Why?

00:30:47.872 --> 00:30:51.838
Mr. Kang, could you take a look at this?

00:30:54.805 --> 00:30:56.405
This is...

00:30:58.972 --> 00:31:00.005
Where did you get this?

00:31:00.005 --> 00:31:04.338
It was found about 200 meters
from the crime scene.

00:31:12.038 --> 00:31:13.833
Right,

00:31:13.833 --> 00:31:15.705
this belongs to Min Ji.

00:31:16.405 --> 00:31:18.172
It's a scarecrow?

00:31:26.572 --> 00:31:30.505
Doesn't it look like she drew it
after seeing the suspect?

00:31:32.838 --> 00:31:34.005
[Kangseng Bookstore]
What did you leave behind?

00:31:34.005 --> 00:31:37.938
My art tube. My drawings are in it.

00:31:39.138 --> 00:31:41.505
This was at the scene?

00:31:42.405 --> 00:31:44.972
You remember these students?

00:31:46.672 --> 00:31:48.172
Oh, this one.

00:31:48.172 --> 00:31:50.472
Yeah, she came by the other day.

00:31:51.805 --> 00:31:52.905
Is this yours?

00:31:52.905 --> 00:31:55.038
Yes, thank you.

00:31:55.038 --> 00:31:58.238
It's late. Do you think
you can go by yourself?

00:31:58.238 --> 00:32:01.238
I'm fine. It's just a quick bus ride.

00:32:01.238 --> 00:32:03.105
Goodbye.

00:32:03.105 --> 00:32:04.772
Goodbye.

00:32:10.905 --> 00:32:13.105
She should've gone home earlier.

00:32:13.105 --> 00:32:15.572
It's really dangerous these days.

00:32:16.361 --> 00:32:19.105
Huh? It's raining.

00:32:20.705 --> 00:32:22.238
This won't do.

00:32:22.238 --> 00:32:24.305
Ki Hwan, I'll bring her
an umbrella and head off first.

00:32:24.305 --> 00:32:25.905
Alright.

00:32:34.438 --> 00:32:35.605
[Kangseng Bookstore]
About what time was that?

00:32:35.605 --> 00:32:40.505
It was right before the bookstore closed,
so just before eight?

00:32:40.505 --> 00:32:42.538
And when did he get home after that?

00:32:42.538 --> 00:32:44.972
Ki Beom? Ki Beom didn't come home.

00:32:44.972 --> 00:32:46.305
What?

00:32:46.305 --> 00:32:47.438
He does that sometimes.

00:32:47.438 --> 00:32:51.438
He hangs out and crashes
at his friends' places.

00:32:51.438 --> 00:32:54.672
Ki Hwan, where is Ki Beom now?

00:32:54.672 --> 00:32:57.072
Why are you acting like this?

00:32:57.072 --> 00:32:58.172
It's...

00:32:58.172 --> 00:33:00.305
- Lee Ki Beom!
- Welcome.

00:33:00.305 --> 00:33:02.338
Lee Ki Beom, come out!

00:33:03.038 --> 00:33:05.105
- Mr. Kim?
- Mr. Kang.

00:33:05.105 --> 00:33:07.072
Mr. Kang, what brings you here?

00:33:07.072 --> 00:33:09.172
This is our team's case.

00:33:10.138 --> 00:33:11.272
What case?

00:33:11.272 --> 00:33:14.072
You know Jeon Kyeong Ho,
the one who got involved with you.

00:33:14.072 --> 00:33:15.072
Yes, what about that punk?

00:33:15.072 --> 00:33:17.205
He was assaulted and taken to the hospital.

00:33:17.205 --> 00:33:18.672
He's unconscious.

00:33:18.672 --> 00:33:20.705
Wait, don't tell me the suspect is...

00:33:20.705 --> 00:33:22.372
Yeah, Lee Ki Beom.

00:33:22.372 --> 00:33:24.338
What? Ki Beom?

00:33:24.338 --> 00:33:26.038
Where is Lee Ki Beom right now?

00:33:26.038 --> 00:33:28.005
Oh, well...

00:33:30.005 --> 00:33:32.472
Let's step outside for a moment and talk.

00:33:33.672 --> 00:33:35.538
I'll call you later.

00:33:38.272 --> 00:33:40.265
So,

00:33:40.265 --> 00:33:42.138
the key witness in a murder case

00:33:42.138 --> 00:33:44.005
is a suspect in another case?

00:33:44.005 --> 00:33:46.538
Yes, and the suspect seems to be on the run.

00:33:46.538 --> 00:33:48.072
Jeon Kyeong Ho again? Seriously?

00:33:48.072 --> 00:33:49.605
Is he faking it again?

00:33:49.605 --> 00:33:51.372
He's a pro at forging medical reports.

00:33:51.372 --> 00:33:52.972
He's actually unconscious this time.

00:33:52.972 --> 00:33:55.005
This is different from the last time
with Mr. Kang.

00:33:55.972 --> 00:33:58.438
I'll step out for a moment.

00:33:58.438 --> 00:34:01.605
What's the rush? Where are you off to now?

00:34:07.405 --> 00:34:09.805
You have a visitor.

00:34:13.891 --> 00:34:15.772
Oh.

00:34:15.772 --> 00:34:16.938
You can clock out now.

00:34:16.938 --> 00:34:18.538
Yes, sir.

00:34:22.405 --> 00:34:27.838
So the last place Kim Min Ji went
before getting killed was that bookstore?

00:34:27.838 --> 00:34:31.505
She may have been with Lee Ki Beom.

00:34:31.505 --> 00:34:33.838
We need Ki Beom's statement.

00:34:34.905 --> 00:34:36.972
[Cha Si Young]
So, about that...

00:34:37.605 --> 00:34:41.438
I'd like to resolve the Jeon Kyeong Ho case
with a settlement.

00:34:41.438 --> 00:34:44.805
Like you said,
assault is prosecuted upon complaint.

00:34:44.805 --> 00:34:49.305
I want you to wrap things up
with Jeon Kyeong Ho.

00:34:50.038 --> 00:34:51.772
Can you do it?

00:34:52.772 --> 00:34:57.272
So we can drop that charge
and take full control of the case?

00:34:59.338 --> 00:35:02.638
Okay, I'll handle Jeon Kyeong Ho.

00:35:02.638 --> 00:35:05.305
You go find Lee Ki Beom first.

00:35:06.172 --> 00:35:07.738
You see?

00:35:07.738 --> 00:35:11.938
Things are easier when we work together.

00:35:11.938 --> 00:35:14.405
You do your job, and I do mine.

00:35:14.405 --> 00:35:16.505
Isn't that perfect?

00:35:19.938 --> 00:35:21.805
Why me?

00:35:21.805 --> 00:35:24.305
There are plenty of capable detectives.

00:35:26.307 --> 00:35:27.838
Well,

00:35:27.838 --> 00:35:30.072
there aren't many people I trust.

00:35:33.238 --> 00:35:35.038
You trust me?

00:35:35.938 --> 00:35:38.505
Why don't you try trusting me too?

00:35:40.805 --> 00:35:43.405
I'll get going. I've got a lot to do.

00:35:44.705 --> 00:35:46.472
Hey, wait,

00:35:46.472 --> 00:35:49.838
aren't you overlooking something?

00:35:49.838 --> 00:35:51.438
Based on what you've said,

00:35:51.438 --> 00:35:56.172
Lee Ki Beom sounds more like a suspect
than a witness.

00:35:56.172 --> 00:35:57.772
Am I wrong?

00:36:12.538 --> 00:36:14.572
Ji Won, Ji Won!

00:36:14.572 --> 00:36:16.972
Why the fuss again? What is it?

00:36:16.972 --> 00:36:18.172
Something big happened.

00:36:18.172 --> 00:36:19.305
What is it?

00:36:19.305 --> 00:36:23.138
Jeon Kyeong Ho was assaulted
and is in a coma.

00:36:23.138 --> 00:36:26.038
What? Who on earth did it?

00:36:26.038 --> 00:36:27.593
Well,

00:36:27.593 --> 00:36:29.772
they say it was Ki Beom.

00:36:30.872 --> 00:36:33.238
Who?

00:36:33.238 --> 00:36:34.338
Attempted murder?

00:36:34.338 --> 00:36:38.105
Well, he had strangulation marks on his neck.

00:36:38.105 --> 00:36:39.838
[Kangseng Police Station]
His condition's not good, either.

00:36:39.838 --> 00:36:42.672
And the suspect? Have they been caught?

00:36:42.672 --> 00:36:44.305
Not yet.

00:36:44.305 --> 00:36:45.938
Sun Young!

00:36:46.938 --> 00:36:48.538
Ji Won.

00:36:51.172 --> 00:36:52.772
What brings you here?

00:36:52.772 --> 00:36:55.138
I came to bring Tae Joo some underwear.

00:36:55.138 --> 00:36:57.505
Did you hear about Jeon Kyeong Ho too?

00:37:00.905 --> 00:37:04.705
We've had a bad history,
but it still doesn't feel right

00:37:04.705 --> 00:37:06.138
that he went through all that.

00:37:06.138 --> 00:37:09.438
Don't take it to heart.
It has nothing to do with you.

00:37:10.172 --> 00:37:12.438
Still, they say it was attempted murder.

00:37:12.438 --> 00:37:15.651
Did the suspect really try
to kill Jeon Kyeong Ho?

00:37:16.972 --> 00:37:18.105
No way, he would never...

00:37:18.105 --> 00:37:19.938
- Huh?
- What?

00:37:21.972 --> 00:37:25.472
I mean, is killing someone that easy?

00:37:25.472 --> 00:37:27.338
Oh, it's hot!

00:37:28.355 --> 00:37:29.872
Oh, no.

00:37:29.872 --> 00:37:32.305
- You're so clumsy, seriously.
- Oh, dear.

00:37:33.372 --> 00:37:35.105
Did you get burned?

00:37:35.105 --> 00:37:36.172
It's okay.

00:37:36.172 --> 00:37:37.572
- Go.
- Yeah, take care.

00:37:37.572 --> 00:37:39.838
- Yeah, bye.
- I'll get going.

00:37:39.838 --> 00:37:42.172
- Take care!
- Yeah.

00:38:10.972 --> 00:38:12.638
Go to hell!

00:38:23.372 --> 00:38:24.505
Help!

00:38:24.505 --> 00:38:26.572
Somebody help!

00:38:31.838 --> 00:38:33.438
Sun Young.

00:38:39.105 --> 00:38:40.738
You...

00:38:46.272 --> 00:38:47.272
Over there!

00:38:47.272 --> 00:38:49.772
Someone collapsed over there! Hurry!

00:38:56.305 --> 00:38:58.272
No one will suspect anything here.

00:38:58.272 --> 00:39:00.605
Don't do this, Sun Young.

00:39:00.605 --> 00:39:02.315
We have nothing to do

00:39:02.315 --> 00:39:04.172
with each other anymore.

00:39:04.172 --> 00:39:06.805
Then why did you do that?

00:39:06.805 --> 00:39:09.772
What am I to you for you to go that far?

00:39:10.505 --> 00:39:13.072
I'll turn myself in.

00:39:15.338 --> 00:39:17.905
I did it.

00:39:17.905 --> 00:39:19.572
I'll take responsibility.

00:39:20.572 --> 00:39:23.238
What if they find out
you went to the protest?

00:39:24.405 --> 00:39:27.838
They say even the student president disappeared
without a trace.

00:39:28.451 --> 00:39:29.897
But...

00:39:32.605 --> 00:39:37.238
Just hide here for now
and see how things unfold.

00:39:40.672 --> 00:39:42.572
Let's run away.

00:39:42.572 --> 00:39:43.572
What are you talking about?

00:39:43.572 --> 00:39:47.105
If you get caught now,
you could be framed with attempted murder.

00:39:49.638 --> 00:39:51.272
What?

00:39:57.321 --> 00:39:58.756
Darn it.

00:40:02.338 --> 00:40:04.405
Are you coming to your senses?

00:40:08.005 --> 00:40:09.438
Oh, dear.

00:40:09.438 --> 00:40:11.838
What are you doing here?

00:40:11.838 --> 00:40:14.505
I heard you need eight weeks to recover.

00:40:14.505 --> 00:40:18.572
Well, you reap what you sow.

00:40:20.105 --> 00:40:22.472
Are you here to mock me?

00:40:22.472 --> 00:40:25.705
That's harsh to someone
who came visit out of concern.

00:40:26.972 --> 00:40:29.538
But why did you go there again?

00:40:29.538 --> 00:40:31.938
Why went to Kang Sun Young?

00:40:32.638 --> 00:40:35.572
To tell her what kind of person you are.

00:40:36.305 --> 00:40:39.438
You told me to counter-sue her
for false accusation

00:40:39.438 --> 00:40:41.385
and frame it as an affair.

00:40:41.385 --> 00:40:44.172
That was all you, Cha Si Young.

00:40:44.172 --> 00:40:46.105
She doesn't know any of that,

00:40:46.105 --> 00:40:49.605
and she was all smiles
and happy to be with you.

00:40:49.605 --> 00:40:52.872
How could you look her in the eye and smile?

00:40:57.005 --> 00:41:00.005
What does that have to do with you?

00:41:00.005 --> 00:41:02.205
Huh?

00:41:02.205 --> 00:41:04.038
Listen carefully.

00:41:04.038 --> 00:41:08.205
The assault was just bad luck.

00:41:08.205 --> 00:41:10.838
You just tripped and fell while walking.

00:41:10.838 --> 00:41:15.172
So drop any thoughts of pressing charges
or anything like that.

00:41:15.172 --> 00:41:17.072
If you understand, nod.

00:41:21.205 --> 00:41:22.205
Why should I?

00:41:22.205 --> 00:41:24.005
So I can be screwed over by you twice?

00:41:24.005 --> 00:41:27.338
No way. My uncle is the county governor.

00:41:28.205 --> 00:41:29.572
Yeah.

00:41:29.572 --> 00:41:34.005
I can make
that title of 'governor's nephew' disappear.

00:41:34.005 --> 00:41:35.529
Okay?

00:41:36.372 --> 00:41:40.705
Want me to put your dear uncle
in cuffs for bribery?

00:41:41.505 --> 00:41:43.672
If you don't believe me,
ask him how much he took.

00:41:43.672 --> 00:41:45.938
Do you think I'm saying this
without evidence?

00:41:48.705 --> 00:41:50.805
Now, answer me.

00:42:01.605 --> 00:42:03.305
Good.

00:42:10.438 --> 00:42:11.705
Why are you doing this to me?

00:42:11.705 --> 00:42:13.872
What did I ever do to you?

00:42:13.872 --> 00:42:15.772
I have no hard feelings toward you.

00:42:15.772 --> 00:42:19.638
It's a request from a dear friend,
so I have no choice.

00:42:20.772 --> 00:42:23.438
Your face is pretty messed up.

00:42:23.438 --> 00:42:26.838
Take care of yourself. Quietly.

00:42:38.857 --> 00:42:41.029
Darn you.

00:42:43.705 --> 00:42:47.938
What now? I said I'd do what you told me!

00:42:50.595 --> 00:42:53.065
Hey, wait...

00:42:53.065 --> 00:42:58.313
No, wait...

00:43:03.105 --> 00:43:05.772
Let me ask one more thing.

00:43:05.772 --> 00:43:08.272
How did you find out about my mother?

00:43:10.438 --> 00:43:12.425
Was that

00:43:12.425 --> 00:43:13.972
Cha Si Young too?

00:43:14.787 --> 00:43:17.411
[Social Affairs Department]

00:43:26.805 --> 00:43:28.438
Oh, this...

00:43:31.299 --> 00:43:33.705
Oh, no.

00:43:33.705 --> 00:43:35.538
It's okay.

00:43:48.305 --> 00:43:53.172
The suspect's handkerchief
is the same as Sun Young's?

00:43:53.172 --> 00:43:54.772
How is that possible?

00:43:59.872 --> 00:44:01.405
[Kangseng Daily]
But see this? He covered his face.

00:44:01.405 --> 00:44:03.105
Ms. Kim Mi Yeon didn't mention that.

00:44:03.105 --> 00:44:06.838
So he only covered his face in front of me?
Why?

00:44:08.372 --> 00:44:10.605
This handkerchief looks familiar.

00:44:14.505 --> 00:44:16.305
This can't be.

00:44:18.772 --> 00:44:20.405
No way.

00:44:21.538 --> 00:44:25.372
[Resignation Letter]

00:44:28.605 --> 00:44:32.905
I didn't realize
you were the superintendent's brother.

00:44:32.905 --> 00:44:36.205
Next time, don't go through him.

00:44:36.205 --> 00:44:38.153
Just tell me directly if you need anything.

00:44:38.153 --> 00:44:41.505
How could a mere prosecutor do that?

00:44:42.638 --> 00:44:45.438
Then I'll take these to him myself.

00:44:45.438 --> 00:44:47.038
- Yes.
- That's okay, right?

00:44:47.038 --> 00:44:48.605
Yes.

00:44:48.605 --> 00:44:50.772
Please tear this up.

00:45:06.605 --> 00:45:08.905
But why did you go there again?

00:45:08.905 --> 00:45:10.805
Why went to Kang Sun Young?

00:45:10.805 --> 00:45:12.638
[Jeon Kyeong Ho]

00:45:12.638 --> 00:45:16.005
To tell her what kind of person you are.

00:45:16.005 --> 00:45:19.105
You told me to counter-sue her
for false accusation

00:45:19.105 --> 00:45:21.033
and frame it as an affair.

00:45:21.033 --> 00:45:23.472
That was all you, Cha Si Young.

00:45:42.672 --> 00:45:45.238
How did you find out about my mother?

00:45:45.238 --> 00:45:46.838
Was that

00:45:47.472 --> 00:45:49.105
Cha Si Young too?

00:45:49.738 --> 00:45:54.705
Cha Si Young was the one
who first brought up your family background.

00:45:55.605 --> 00:45:57.638
Thinking back now,

00:45:57.638 --> 00:45:59.938
it was all bait.

00:46:09.138 --> 00:46:13.772
[Kang Tae Joo, son of a bar hostess]

00:46:13.772 --> 00:46:15.738
Hey! Get out of the way!

00:46:16.745 --> 00:46:18.409
Darn it.

00:46:26.563 --> 00:46:27.721
Darn it.

00:46:42.538 --> 00:46:44.872
Oh, Kang Tae Joo!

00:46:47.272 --> 00:46:50.405
I wrapped up the Jeon Kyeong Ho case nicely.

00:46:50.405 --> 00:46:52.872
You won't be bothered anymore.

00:46:52.872 --> 00:46:55.105
I took care of your resignation too.

00:46:55.105 --> 00:46:57.538
Now just focus on the investigation.

00:47:03.005 --> 00:47:04.297
Why?

00:47:04.297 --> 00:47:06.038
Something wrong?

00:47:07.105 --> 00:47:08.872
Why did you do that?

00:47:09.505 --> 00:47:12.205
- What?
- Why did you do that to my sister?

00:47:15.572 --> 00:47:17.738
What did you gain from it?

00:47:21.072 --> 00:47:23.038
- It's a misunderstanding.
- A misunderstanding?

00:47:26.405 --> 00:47:28.038
Fine, you won't believe anything I say.

00:47:28.038 --> 00:47:29.609
But

00:47:29.609 --> 00:47:32.372
I was trying to help you in my own way.

00:47:32.372 --> 00:47:35.038
That's just nonsense.

00:47:35.038 --> 00:47:37.038
Tae Joo.

00:47:37.038 --> 00:47:38.905
Don't you trust me?

00:47:38.905 --> 00:47:40.805
Man, that hurts.

00:47:40.805 --> 00:47:43.305
I'm trying this hard.

00:47:47.372 --> 00:47:49.545
Then

00:47:49.545 --> 00:47:52.472
why did you do that to me back then?

00:47:52.472 --> 00:47:53.505
Back then?

00:47:53.505 --> 00:47:55.372
Back then.

00:47:55.372 --> 00:47:57.772
I begged you.

00:47:57.772 --> 00:48:02.372
I got beaten like a dog and pleaded.

00:48:02.372 --> 00:48:05.205
I begged you not to say
that one thing, but...

00:48:05.938 --> 00:48:07.538
Why did you do that?

00:48:08.638 --> 00:48:10.272
Huh?

00:48:14.272 --> 00:48:16.172
You can't answer, can you?

00:48:16.838 --> 00:48:18.672
Because there was no reason.

00:48:20.072 --> 00:48:22.638
It was just a joke to you.

00:48:22.638 --> 00:48:24.138
Does that even matter?

00:48:24.138 --> 00:48:25.772
What?

00:48:26.805 --> 00:48:29.372
It's all in the past.

00:48:29.372 --> 00:48:30.972
Wow, in the past?

00:48:30.972 --> 00:48:33.538
Tae Joo, the past is just the past.

00:48:33.538 --> 00:48:37.938
What matters is
what you and I will do together going forward.

00:48:37.938 --> 00:48:42.305
Why should we always be held back
by something so trivial?

00:48:42.305 --> 00:48:44.905
I said I'd do better from now on.

00:48:44.905 --> 00:48:47.672
Let's just forget everything and start fresh.

00:48:47.672 --> 00:48:50.572
Why do you always have to ruin it?

00:48:50.572 --> 00:48:52.205
Tae Joo.

00:48:56.005 --> 00:49:00.638
Cut me some slack just once, okay?

00:49:00.638 --> 00:49:03.638
I'll do better, I promise.

00:49:03.638 --> 00:49:05.238
Okay, Kang Tae Joo?

00:49:07.938 --> 00:49:10.057
Why does it have to be now,

00:49:10.057 --> 00:49:12.238
of all times?

00:49:12.872 --> 00:49:14.472
What?

00:49:15.238 --> 00:49:17.005
Forget it?

00:49:17.005 --> 00:49:18.005
Who says I can just forget?

00:49:18.005 --> 00:49:21.238
Do you think I remember it because I want to?

00:49:22.872 --> 00:49:24.872
Cha Si Young.

00:49:24.872 --> 00:49:27.505
I'll make sure you remember this clearly too.

00:49:28.172 --> 00:49:31.172
You're the one
who insisted on messing with me,

00:49:31.172 --> 00:49:34.772
back then, and now.

00:49:34.772 --> 00:49:36.372
Tae Joo!

00:49:40.305 --> 00:49:42.938
I found the owner of the handkerchief.

00:49:42.938 --> 00:49:44.538
Hurry.

00:49:48.772 --> 00:49:51.005
Handkerchief?

00:49:51.005 --> 00:49:52.838
The owner?

00:50:05.505 --> 00:50:07.155
This is

00:50:07.155 --> 00:50:09.305
Sun Young's handkerchief?

00:50:10.205 --> 00:50:12.338
- See the embroidery here?
- Yeah.

00:50:14.272 --> 00:50:16.905
Sun Young made this herself.

00:50:16.905 --> 00:50:21.172
The only person who could have a matching one
is Ki Beom.

00:50:25.005 --> 00:50:26.638
Wait a second.

00:50:27.427 --> 00:50:29.272
[Choi Min Ja Case Report]

00:50:29.272 --> 00:50:32.038
[Non-Prosecution Decision Log]
You're thinking what I'm thinking, right?

00:50:33.405 --> 00:50:35.205
That's impossible.

00:50:36.738 --> 00:50:38.538
That kid...

00:50:39.272 --> 00:50:41.572
There's no way he'd do that.

00:50:41.572 --> 00:50:43.705
Oh, Ms. Seo, you're here.

00:50:43.705 --> 00:50:45.605
Hello.

00:50:45.605 --> 00:50:47.905
Ms. Sun Young came by during the day.

00:50:47.905 --> 00:50:49.438
The underwear and socks are there.

00:50:49.438 --> 00:50:52.649
Right, earlier Sun Young
was talking about Jeon Kyeong Ho.

00:50:52.649 --> 00:50:54.305
Did you bring it up first, Mr. Park?

00:50:54.305 --> 00:50:55.438
No.

00:50:55.438 --> 00:50:56.605
She already knew about it.

00:50:56.605 --> 00:50:58.238
Sun Young knew
what happened to Jeon Kyeong Ho?

00:50:58.238 --> 00:51:00.672
- Yes.
- How?

00:51:00.672 --> 00:51:04.038
I just assumed you had told her, sir.

00:51:08.329 --> 00:51:10.138
Oh, Mr. Park.

00:51:10.138 --> 00:51:11.172
Yes.

00:51:11.172 --> 00:51:14.405
Get as many officers as you can right now

00:51:14.405 --> 00:51:16.338
and search the entire area
around my place for Lee Ki Beom.

00:51:16.338 --> 00:51:18.505
Yes, sir!

00:51:18.505 --> 00:51:20.072
Hey!

00:51:20.072 --> 00:51:23.005
- Tae...
- Tae Joo, I drove Sun Young home earlier.

00:51:26.338 --> 00:51:28.872
[Kang Tae Joo]

00:51:33.372 --> 00:51:34.905
No intercity buses.

00:51:34.905 --> 00:51:39.105
Let's just get to Heesong Station first
and take a train from there.

00:51:39.772 --> 00:51:41.405
Ki Beom!

00:51:41.405 --> 00:51:44.538
Ki Beom! What are you doing?

00:51:44.538 --> 00:51:46.605
Ki Beom, open it!

00:51:47.238 --> 00:51:50.138
Ki Beom!

00:51:59.838 --> 00:52:01.505
Ki Beom!

00:52:35.305 --> 00:52:37.938
He must have gone to the bus stop.

00:56:03.372 --> 00:56:05.638
Sun Young!

00:56:05.638 --> 00:56:06.738
Are you okay?

00:56:06.738 --> 00:56:09.038
Open your eyes!

00:56:09.038 --> 00:56:11.105
Sun Young!

00:56:11.105 --> 00:56:12.705
Sun Young!

00:56:52.905 --> 00:56:55.805
Tae Joo, this...

00:57:00.372 --> 00:57:03.238
What kind of clothes are these?

00:57:03.238 --> 00:57:05.605
Don't walk alone at night.

00:57:05.605 --> 00:57:07.205
Sun Young!

00:57:09.072 --> 00:57:10.105
Tae Joo!

00:57:10.105 --> 00:57:11.105
Ji Won, you stay here.

00:57:11.105 --> 00:57:12.238
- Let's go together!
- People are coming.

00:57:12.238 --> 00:57:14.105
Tell them what happened.

00:57:18.072 --> 00:57:19.705
Sun Young!

00:57:22.305 --> 00:57:23.905
Sun Young!

00:57:26.638 --> 00:57:28.305
Kang Sun Young!

00:57:29.505 --> 00:57:31.738
Sun Young, please...

00:57:31.738 --> 00:57:33.438
Kang Sun Young!

00:57:33.438 --> 00:57:34.705
Who's there?

00:57:34.705 --> 00:57:35.772
It's me, Tae Joo.

00:57:35.772 --> 00:57:37.205
Cha Si Young?

00:57:37.205 --> 00:57:39.538
Did you fire the shot?

00:57:39.538 --> 00:57:41.205
Hey!

00:57:43.238 --> 00:57:44.272
Sun Young!

00:57:44.272 --> 00:57:46.372
Hey, Sun Young...

00:57:46.372 --> 00:57:47.538
What happened?

00:57:47.538 --> 00:57:48.538
Hey, Sun Young!

00:57:48.538 --> 00:57:51.972
Don't worry. She just passed out.

00:57:51.972 --> 00:57:53.772
- Hey, Sun Young!
- That punk

00:57:53.772 --> 00:57:55.805
was after Sun Young.

00:57:59.872 --> 00:58:01.772
Sun Young, wake up.

00:58:01.772 --> 00:58:03.405
Sun Young!

00:58:05.538 --> 00:58:07.138
Hey, Cha Si Young!

00:58:09.638 --> 00:58:11.738
What's wrong with you?

00:58:11.738 --> 00:58:13.338
Cha Si Young!

00:58:20.072 --> 00:58:22.538
Hey, what just happened?

00:58:22.538 --> 00:58:23.772
Are you okay?

00:58:23.772 --> 00:58:25.372
Hey, Cha Si Young!

00:58:26.772 --> 00:58:28.372
I...

00:58:29.405 --> 00:58:31.872
Actually, I knew.

00:58:31.872 --> 00:58:33.513
That you

00:58:33.513 --> 00:58:36.005
always packed snacks for your sister.

00:58:36.005 --> 00:58:38.738
Why bring that up all of a sudden?
Shut up, you punk!

00:58:40.138 --> 00:58:41.897
If I hadn't gone

00:58:41.897 --> 00:58:44.672
just to deliver that back then,

00:58:45.738 --> 00:58:47.638
we'd have been fine, right?

00:58:47.638 --> 00:58:50.372
I told you to shut up, you punk!

00:58:53.205 --> 00:58:55.705
Get Sun Young something to eat.
She's been whining since earlier.

00:58:55.705 --> 00:58:57.338
Mom!

00:58:58.505 --> 00:59:00.905
Can I go to college?

00:59:00.905 --> 00:59:04.138
Go, earn the money and go.

00:59:30.038 --> 00:59:31.738
Father...

00:59:57.305 --> 00:59:58.938
I thought

01:00:00.105 --> 01:00:01.705
you were

01:00:02.505 --> 01:00:05.372
my father's son.

01:00:09.305 --> 01:00:10.793
But

01:00:10.793 --> 01:00:13.905
I can't stand brothers.

01:00:14.938 --> 01:00:17.138
Friends are fine, though.

01:00:23.172 --> 01:00:25.438
- I feel dizzy...
- Hey, Cha Si Young!

01:00:25.438 --> 01:00:28.405
Stay with me, man!

01:00:28.405 --> 01:00:29.405
No!

01:00:29.405 --> 01:00:33.005
Hey, you punk! Stay with me!

01:00:33.005 --> 01:00:34.138
Cha Si Young!

01:00:34.138 --> 01:00:36.438
Hey, man, come to your senses!

01:00:37.105 --> 01:00:38.738
Hey, Cha Si Young!

01:01:30.272 --> 01:01:32.172
Got you!

01:01:32.972 --> 01:01:35.372
You little rat!

01:02:13.105 --> 01:02:15.005
[Keep Quiet]
You can't come in.

01:02:23.738 --> 01:02:26.305
[In Surgery]

01:02:26.305 --> 01:02:27.672
[Restricted Area]

01:02:27.672 --> 01:02:29.305
Si Young.

01:02:30.638 --> 01:02:31.805
Don't die.

01:02:31.805 --> 01:02:33.772
[Operating Room]

01:02:33.772 --> 01:02:35.405
Please...

01:02:42.238 --> 01:02:44.138
Oh, come on. Tell me.

01:02:45.005 --> 01:02:47.205
You trusted that person once, didn't you?

01:02:49.605 --> 01:02:51.505
No, never. Not even once.

01:02:51.505 --> 01:02:55.205
Come on, then how could you
even team up with someone like that?

01:02:55.205 --> 01:02:57.372
This is no fun.

01:02:57.372 --> 01:03:00.305
Professor, I can tell you're lying.

01:03:04.938 --> 01:03:07.972
Do you still keep in touch with him?

01:03:08.938 --> 01:03:10.572
No.

01:03:11.572 --> 01:03:14.438
Do you know how he's doing now?

01:03:15.272 --> 01:03:16.905
I don't.

01:03:18.738 --> 01:03:20.805
Another lie.

01:03:24.169 --> 01:03:28.705
You're worse at lying than I expected.

01:03:29.338 --> 01:03:31.905
That's a bit unfair, isn't it?

01:03:34.105 --> 01:03:36.105
This is your last chance.

01:03:36.105 --> 01:03:38.038
No more lies this time.

01:03:38.038 --> 01:03:40.705
Or no more visits from now on.

01:03:45.138 --> 01:03:47.505
Did teaming up with that friend

01:03:47.505 --> 01:03:51.905
become a turning point
in your life, Professor?

01:03:53.205 --> 01:03:55.338
Was it for the better,

01:03:56.072 --> 01:03:58.072
or for the worse?

01:04:01.838 --> 01:04:03.705
The worse.

01:04:05.805 --> 01:04:08.105
Because I lost everything.

01:04:08.772 --> 01:04:10.572
You're lying again...

01:04:17.738 --> 01:04:19.572
Wait, it's true?

01:04:28.305 --> 01:04:30.438
I lost everything.

01:05:02.705 --> 01:05:03.705
Kang Sun Young, who is it?

01:05:03.705 --> 01:05:04.872
You're not seriously
suspecting Ki Beom, are you?

01:05:04.872 --> 01:05:06.438
If it wasn't Lee Ki Beom, who was it?

01:05:06.438 --> 01:05:07.605
It's all circumstantial evidence.

01:05:07.605 --> 01:05:09.138
You are still not sure

01:05:09.138 --> 01:05:11.172
that Lee Ki Beom is the killer?

01:05:11.172 --> 01:05:12.872
A murder case?

01:05:12.872 --> 01:05:13.938
How many times is this now?

01:05:13.938 --> 01:05:15.372
Can anyone even live like this?

01:05:15.372 --> 01:05:17.438
- We will catch the killer.
- Then do your darn job.

01:05:17.438 --> 01:05:19.705
He escaped the scene
and hid at Lee Joo Hee's house.

01:05:19.705 --> 01:05:21.338
The route lines up perfectly.
So does the timeline.

01:05:21.338 --> 01:05:23.472
Even now, you still think
Lee Ki Beom isn't the real killer?

01:05:23.472 --> 01:05:26.072
Are you suspecting Ki Beom too?

01:05:26.072 --> 01:05:28.172
Ki Beom is a serial murder suspect.

01:05:28.172 --> 01:05:30.638
We must find Ki Beom, ma'am.